HEADWORD: Stellular
<hw>Stel"lu*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stellula</ets>, dim. of <ets>stella</ets> a star.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the shape or appearance of little stars;
radiated.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Marked with starlike spots of color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stellulate</ent>⟦br⟧
